    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>RUSSIA TO RAISE OIL TAX</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Sabrina Tavernise</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tavernise, Sabrina</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Russian government will impose at least 35 percent increase on crude oil export tax on Aug 1, move to provide additional budget revenue from rising world demand and higher prices; will raise duty to 27 euros, or about $25 a metric ton, from current 20 euros; Deputy Prime Min Viktor Khristenko says if price of oil exceeds $29 a barrel on Aug 1, government will raise duty to 34 euros a metric ton--a 70 percent increase; photo (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Russian government will impose at least a 35 percent increase on a crude oil export tax on Aug. 1, a move to provide additional budget revenue from rising world demand and higher prices. Russia will raise the duty to 27 euros, or about $25 a metric ton, from the current 20 euros, Russian news agencies quoted Deputy Prime Minister Viktor Khristenko. If the price of oil exceeds $29 a barrel on Aug. 1, the government will raise the duty to 34 euros a metric ton -- a 70 percent increase.</p>
        <p>Sabrina Tavernise (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
